 given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Priscot was born about 1385, in England, United Kingdom. She married Paul Dayrell in 1402, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1385–Deceased":"umbes 1385–Surnud","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1405–1510":"1405–1510","1385–Female":"1385–Surnud","1510":"1510","Abt 1385":"umbes 1385","1385":"1385","1380":"1380","1405":"1405","Lillingston, Dairell, England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1385–Deceased":"noin 1385–Kuollut","1380–Male":"1380–Kuollut","1405–1510":"1405–1510","1385–Female":"1385–Kuollut","1510":"1510","Abt 1385":"noin 1385","1385":"1385","1380":"1380","1405":"1405","Lillingston, Dairell, England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1385–Deceased":"environ 1385–Décédée","1380–Male":"1380–Décédé","1405–1510":"1405–1510","1385–Female":"1385–Décédée","1510":"1510","Abt 1385":"environ 1385","1385":"1385","1380":"1380","1405":"1405","Lillingston, Dairell, England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Margaret Priscot est née environ 1385, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Paul Dayrell en 1402, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"Abt 1385–Deceased":"um 1385–Verstorben","1380–Male":"1380–Verstorben","1405–1510":"1405–1510","1385–Female":"1385–Verstorben","1510":"1510","Abt 1385":"um 1385","1385":"1385","1380":"1380","1405":"1405","Lillingston, Dairell, England, United Kingdom":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Margaret Priscot wurde um 1385 in England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hat 1402 in England Paul Dayrell geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"Abt 1385–Deceased":"about 1385–Desede","1380–Male":"1380–Desede","1405–1510":"1405–1510","1385–Female":"1385–Desede","1510":"1510","Abt 1385":"about 1385","1385":"1385","1380":"1380","1405":"14